      "content": "i see, so basically just stick to the western suit look everywhere. what about when people want to incorporate their own heritage or traditional clothing? like if someone is attending a top-level summit in india or nigeria and they want to wear something like a high-quality sari or an agbada to show their status/professionalism, how does that fit into your \"global standard\"? is that seen as being \"sophisticated\" or does it just count as \"cultural attire\" instead of the professional baseline?",
