      "content": "When highly skilled and well-executed, wearing traditional attire in places like India or Nigeria is seen as a powerful display of cultural confidence and status, not a deviation from professionalism. The key is quality; the fabric must be luxurious, the tailoring flawless, and the presentation immaculate to meet the \"high-level\" standard. In these contexts, mastering and elevating local formal wear *is* often the most sophisticated baseline, showing respect and deep understanding of the environment.",
